parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or fail to accelerate, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls
jerks
or fails to accelerate; gear shift stuck in park; transmission control system malfunction; rough shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalls
fails to restart
or runs rough; vehicle jerks or lurches forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience other safety issues.
symptoms: Airbag light illuminates; check engine light illuminates; vehicle alarm system malfunctions; TPMS light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and gear shift problems can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or fail to accelerate, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; clutch pedal sticks to the floor; gear shift stuck in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake manifold runner control problems can cause the vehicle to stall, run rough, or experience other performance issues.
symptoms: Check engine light illuminates; intake manifold runner control stuck open; vehicle runs rough or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and experience various electrical issues, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
the battery light comes on
the check engine light comes on
the horn sounds intermittently
the wipers stop working
the lights flicker
the airbag light stays on
and the vehicle experiences loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause the vehicle to experience various electrical issues, including stalling, loss of power, and intermittent horn sounds, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The horn sounds intermittently
the wipers stop working
the lights flicker
the vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
and the electrical system experiences malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Electronic Throttle Control system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ETC warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle hesitates to accelerate
the vehicle shakes or vibrates
the engine RPMs fluctuate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to engage or disengage
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The gear shift getting stuck in park can cause the vehicle to be unable to move, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shift gets stuck in park
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intake Manifold and Sensor Switch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold and sensor switch can cause the vehicle to lose power or acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the check engine warning light illuminates.
